Yumi Browser — Authors and Contributors
=======================================

Yumi Browser is a deliberately solo-developer project. The maintainer
listed below is the sole author of the original code in this repository.
External code contributions are not accepted at this time; see
CONTRIBUTING.md for the rationale.

Maintainer
----------

Isaac (DevNullIsaac on Codeberg) <devnullisaac@gmail.com>
    Project lead and sole developer. Original author of the host
    runtime, the cryptographic glue, the group registrar, the
    peer-to-peer network stack, and the WebAssembly sandbox host.

Third-Party Code Authors
------------------------

Yumi Browser vendors source files written by other authors. Their work
is acknowledged here as a matter of attribution; they are not
contributors to Yumi Browser itself, and inclusion in this list does
not imply endorsement by them of this project. See THIRD_PARTY.md for
the full record and licensing.

  - The Skein team (Bruce Schneier, Niels Ferguson, Stefan Lucks,
    Doug Whiting, Mihir Bellare, Tadayoshi Kohno, Jon Callas,
    Jesse Walker) — Skein-1024 / Threefish-1024 reference
    implementation, public domain.
  - Dr Brian Gladman — portable endian/type headers
    (`src/crypto/brg_endian.h`, `src/crypto/brg_types.h`).

Yumi Browser additionally builds on a substantial set of upstream
dependencies under `deps/` (OpenSSL, oqs-provider, SDL, Wasmer, Dawn,
DuckDB, Slang, FFmpeg, FreeType, HarfBuzz, ICU, LibRaw, libjuice,
bzip2, libjpeg-turbo, and others). The authors and contributors of
those projects are not listed here individually; their authorship is
recorded in their own repositories.
